        "subject": "LU-19274 contrib: Add spelling check to checkpatch-man",
        "message": "LU-19274 contrib: Add spelling check to checkpatch-man\n\nThis patch adds:\n- 'hunspell' check to checkpatch-man.pl.\n- Custom dictionary (contrib/scripts/exa.dic) is\n  separate from patch 62211 for easier landing;\n  will be merged after 62211 lands.\n- -s option to see verbose spelling warnings. By default\n  this is switch off.\n- adds under summary count of spelling errors found\n- if 'hunspell' binary is not found it skips spell check\n  and reports \"spelling check not done\" under summary\n- spell_dict is populated after reading file spelling-man.txt\n  currently this is not being used.\n\nSummary report with 'hunspell':\ntotal: 0 errors, 2 warnings, 3 checks, 281 lines checked, 0 spelling errors\n\nSummary report without 'hunspell':\ntotal: 0 errors, 2 warnings, 3 checks, 281 lines checked, spelling check not done\n\nThis is first of the series, there would be 1 or 2 followup\npatches which will be run individually on all Documentation/man*\nfolder and lustre key-word added to lustre_spell.en.pms\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Arshad Hussain <arshad.hussain@aeoncomputing.com>\nChange-Id: I4a47ab43abc52e7512ad8e347dd772b7d0f8f067\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/60992\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nReviewed-by: Frederick Dilger <fdilger@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
